I"_<p>Antonio Damasio suggests that <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/affect-reflects-ideological-structures">emotion</a> is not incompatible with <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/logic-frameworks-formalize-truth">reason</a>. He argues that <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/affect-reflects-ideological-structures">emotion</a> is essential in <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/logic-frameworks-formalize-truth">reason</a>, in that it provides <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/metabolism-influences-neural-dynamics">useful heuristics driven by gut feelings</a> which enable the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/prototypical-reasoning-enriches-exemplars">reasoner</a> to <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/candidate-solution-overload-is-a-problem">effectively navigate the problem space</a>.</p>
